# Commit Message Metadata

When creating git commits that include a `Co-authored-by` trailer, add model and option metadata **immediately after** that line.

## Format

```
<commit subject and body>

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Model: <model display name>
<option>: <value>
<option>: <value>
```

- Use the model's display name (e.g. `Composer 2.5`, `Sonnet 4.6`), not internal slugs.
- List each relevant option on its own line as `Key: value`.
- Include only options that were set or are meaningful for the session (e.g. MAX Mode, Fast, Effort, Thinking, Context).

## Examples

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Model: Composer 2.5
MAX Mode: true
Fast: false
```

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Model: Sonnet 4.6
Effort: High
Thinking: true
Context: 200K
```
